	(text "Design values:\n Standing current: 10 mA (5 mA each branch)\n Triode gm: ~5-6 mA/V (per datasheet)\n\nComponent references based on left channel numbering\n\nNode calculations (quiescent):\n Around triodes:\n  Triode gates: 0V\n  Triode Cathodes: 0.7V\n  R211, R212 voltage divider: 133k * (30V-0.7V) / (20k + 133k) = 25.5V\n  Triode anodes: cascode gate voltage - Vbe = 24.8V\n  Cascode fc, target 1Hz: C > 1/(2*pi*R212*1Hz) = 1.2 uF, using 4.7uF\n\n Current mirror:\n  Choose R203,206 for Vdrop = 250 mV\n  R203,206 = 250mV/5mA = 50 Ohm\n  Q205: Vc = Ve+Vbe = 0.9V (from 30V)\n  Q201: Vc = Ic,vas*Re,vas + 2*Vbe,BD140 = .01A*20R + 1.3 = 1.5V\n\n Constant current source:\n  Vb,Q207: Vbe = 0.65 V (over -30V)\n  I,R204: 0.65V/65R = 10 mA\n  VB,Q204: Vg,Q207 + Vbe = 1.3 V (over -30V)\n  Ic,Q207: (30-1.3)/20k = 1.44 mA\n  Vb,Q203: -1.44mA * 10k = -14.4V (wrt GND)\n  C201: filters rail noise, sees 10k||10k\n   For fc = 1Hz, use C > 1/(2*pi*10k||10k*1Hz) = 32uF, using 47 uF\n\nPower consumption (worst-case):\n Worst case in each component, hard current swing into one branch\n R203,206: P = (10mA)^2 * 50 Ohm = 5 mW\n Q201: P = 10mA * Vce,mirror = 10mA * 1.5V = 15 mW\n Q205: P = 10 mA * Vbe = 6.5 mW\n Q202,Q206: P = 10 mA * Vce ~= .01A * 5V = 50 mW\n Tube: P = 10 mA * Vak = .01A * 25V = 250 mW\n Q203: P = 10 mA * Vce = .01A * 15V = 150 mW\n Q204: P = 10 mA * Vce = .01A * 15V = 150 mW\n R204: P = (10 mA)*2 * R = 6.5 mW\n Q207: P = 1.44 mA * 2Vbe = .00144A * 1.3V = 1.87 mW\n R208,R209: P = (1.44mA)^2 * 10k = 20 mW\n R211,R212: I = 29.3V/(20k+133k) = .2 mA, P = (.2mA)^2 * R = 0.8mW, 5.23 mW\n\n Total for stage: P = Ic * (Vcc-Vee) = .01A*60V = 600 mW\n Total for current mirror bias: .00144A*30V = 32.2 mW"
